49#include <openssl/aes.h>
50
51#include <assert.h>
52
53#include "../aes/internal.h"
54#include "../modes/internal.h"
55
56
57void AES_ctr128_encrypt(const uint8_t *in, uint8_t *out, size_t len,
58 const AES_KEY *key, uint8_t ivec[AES_BLOCK_SIZE],
59 uint8_t ecount_buf[AES_BLOCK_SIZE], unsigned int *num) {
60 if (hwaes_capable()) {
61 CRYPTO_ctr128_encrypt_ctr32(in, out, len, key, ivec, ecount_buf, num,
62 aes_hw_ctr32_encrypt_blocks);
63 } else if (vpaes_capable()) {
64#if defined(VPAES_CTR32)
65 // TODO(davidben): On ARM, where |BSAES| is additionally defined, this could
66 // use |vpaes_ctr32_encrypt_blocks_with_bsaes|.
67 CRYPTO_ctr128_encrypt_ctr32(in, out, len, key, ivec, ecount_buf, num,
68 vpaes_ctr32_encrypt_blocks);
69#else
70 CRYPTO_ctr128_encrypt(in, out, len, key, ivec, ecount_buf, num,
71 vpaes_encrypt);
72#endif
73 } else {
74 CRYPTO_ctr128_encrypt_ctr32(in, out, len, key, ivec, ecount_buf, num,
75 aes_nohw_ctr32_encrypt_blocks);
76 }
77}
78
79void AES_ecb_encrypt(const uint8_t *in, uint8_t *out, const AES_KEY *key,
80 const int enc) {
81 assert(in && out && key);
82 assert((AES_ENCRYPT == enc) || (AES_DECRYPT == enc));
83
84 if (AES_ENCRYPT == enc) {
85 AES_encrypt(in, out, key);
86 } else {
87 AES_decrypt(in, out, key);
88 }
89}
90
91void AES_cbc_encrypt(const uint8_t *in, uint8_t *out, size_t len,
92 const AES_KEY *key, uint8_t *ivec, const int enc) {
93 if (hwaes_capable()) {
94 aes_hw_cbc_encrypt(in, out, len, key, ivec, enc);
95 return;
96 }
97
98 if (!vpaes_capable()) {
99 aes_nohw_cbc_encrypt(in, out, len, key, ivec, enc);
100 return;
101 }
102 if (enc) {
103 CRYPTO_cbc128_encrypt(in, out, len, key, ivec, AES_encrypt);
104 } else {
105 CRYPTO_cbc128_decrypt(in, out, len, key, ivec, AES_decrypt);
106 }
107}
108
109void AES_ofb128_encrypt(const uint8_t *in, uint8_t *out, size_t length,
110 const AES_KEY *key, uint8_t *ivec, int *num) {
111 unsigned num_u = (unsigned)(*num);
112 CRYPTO_ofb128_encrypt(in, out, length, key, ivec, &num_u, AES_encrypt);
113 *num = (int)num_u;
114}
115
116void AES_cfb128_encrypt(const uint8_t *in, uint8_t *out, size_t length,
117 const AES_KEY *key, uint8_t *ivec, int *num,
118 int enc) {
119 unsigned num_u = (unsigned)(*num);
120 CRYPTO_cfb128_encrypt(in, out, length, key, ivec, &num_u, enc, AES_encrypt);
121 *num = (int)num_u;
122}
